#2050
@@yThe Sunward Caravan Way@@N~
@@yA broad ribbon of packed sand runs perfectly east and west, bordered by low cairns painted with faded @@ygold@@y that still catch the sun.
@@bHigh above, a clean blue vault throws sharp light across wagon ruts, and each gust carries the dry rasp of distant dunes sliding against stone.
@@yEven with no travelers in sight, the road feels alive with old commerce, as if caravans passed only moments ago and left their heat in the ground.@@N
@@yThe straight alignment makes travel simple, but the silence beyond the road reminds you how quickly a single step off-course can turn hostile.@@N
