@@bBluewind Trade Road@@N~
@@yThe caravan way here is hard-packed and disciplined, a deliberate line cut through restless desert that refuses to stay still for long.
@@bBlue-shadowed drifts gather at the margins while sun-burnished marker stones stand like patient sentries counting miles to the east.
@@yYour steps stir fine dust that glitters briefly before vanishing, swallowed by a wind that never quite stops speaking.@@N
@@yThe straight alignment makes travel simple, but the silence beyond the road reminds you how quickly a single step off-course can turn hostile.@@N
